simergy.events

Class Event

  • java.lang.Object
    • simergy.events.Event
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    EventOperations
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Consultation, Examination, Outcome, PatientArrival, Registration, TestTransportation, Transportation

    public abstract class Event
extends java.lang.Object
implements EventOperations
    The Class Event. This abstract class defines what information an event should contain. An event belongs to a workflow. That workflow is used to store persistent information about the ED in witch the event occur, the patient affected by the event etc... This class is very important to handle the particularity and differences of each kind of event through polymorphism. The resources needed by an event are represented by a HashMap.

    • Method Detail

      • update

        public void update()
        Description copied from interface: EventOperations
        Updates the event. First it checks if the event is started or not. If not and if all the requirements are good, it starts the event. Then it checks if the event is in progress and if the ED time is equal to the event's end time. If that's the case, it ends the event.
        Specified by:
        update in interface EventOperations
        See Also:
        EventOperations.requirementsAllGood(), EventOperations.startEvent(), EventOperations.endEvent()

      • requirementsAllGood

        public boolean requirementsAllGood()
        Description copied from interface: EventOperations
        Checks if all the requirements to start an event are good. That means that all the resources needed are available and that the patient is the next to come in his physician or health service waiting queue.
        Specified by:
        requirementsAllGood in interface EventOperations
        Returns:
        true, if successful

      • startEvent

        public void startEvent()
                throws EventStartFailedException
        Description copied from interface: EventOperations
        Starts the event. Sets the end time of the event. Sets the patient's state to VISITING and assign all the needed resources to the event. This method can be overridden in the subclasses to perform specific actions in particular examples.
